text: Stocks finally paused after a long upward run.

title: Tesla unveils Model Y
text: Sibile Marcellus, Dan Roberts and Aikiko Fujita of Yahoo Finance discuss the new Tesla automobile that some say is closer to an SUV than the other Tesla models.

title: Tesla names new CFO, chief accounting officer; stock gains
text: Tesla Inc.  disclosed Thursday that it appointed Zachary Kirkhorn as its chief financial officer, succeeding Deepak Ahuja who is retiring.

title: Tesla's Model Y sales goals 'aggressive,' analyst says
text: Tesla Inc.  sales targets for the Model Y crossover, which the car maker expects to unveil today at 8 p.m. Pacific, are on net "aggressive," said Toni Sacconaghi, an analyst at Bernstein.

title: Tesla's Kirkhorn takes over as CFO. Corporate Controller Taneja promoted to Chief Accounting Officer
text: Tesla's new CFO officially took office Wednesday, the company said in a filing. The company also promoted its corporate controller Vaibhav Taneja to the role of Chief Accounting Officer.

title: Tesla steps into hottest auto segment with Model Y debut Thursday
text: Tesla dives into one of the hottest auto segments with the long-awaited debut of its Model Y crossover utility Thursday night.

title: Why legendary investor Ron Baron is betting big on Tesla
text: Ron Baron, chairman and CEO of Baron Capital, sits down with "Squawk Box" to explain why he has decided to invest long-term in Tesla despite analysts shying away from the stock.

title: The Wild Ride of Elon Musk and the Tesla Whistleblower
text: Mar.13 -- In June of 2018, a Business Insider article detailed how inefficiency at Tesla's Gigafactory in Nevada cost the company around $150 million. That information came from a whistleblower that the electric-car maker believed to be Martin Tripp, a former employee. But, since then the story has been one wild ride after another. Bloomberg's Matt Robinson has more on "Bloomberg Technology."

title: DOD could suspend Elon Musk’s security clearance
text: FBN’s Charlie Gasparino on the controversies surrounding Tesla CEO Elon Musk and how the DOD may suspend the Tesla CEO’s security clearance.

title: Tesla: Beware Of A Dead Cat Bounce
text: Tesla’s shares have been falling since its recent high in mid-December and took another leg down in March after Elon Musk announced the $35,000 Model 3 and closing most of the company's stores.

title: 12 Tesla Questions The SEC Should Ask Musk At The Evidentiary Hearing
text: Elon Musk filed his response to the SEC on March 11. The SEC in turn asked the judge to file a response, which will happen by March 19.

title: Elon Musk Admits A Mistake

title: Model 3 Demand Is Potentially a Lot More Than Expected, Tesla Analyst Rusch Says

title: Why China Could Make Or Break Tesla
text: n January, Tesla started building a Gigafactory in China, the company's first outside of the United States. Elon Musk says that Model 3s will be coming out of China by the end of 2019, but Tesla is known for setting unrealistic goals.

title: Tesla issues $13.8 million in stock to buy trailers to transport cars from factory floor to customers
text: Instead of cash, the electric car maker used 49,967 shares at a maximum price of $277.05 a share as of Feb. 12 to buy the trailers from Central Valley Auto Transport, a California company that specializes in car carriers.

title: Tilson Vs. Left: Short Sellers Place $10,000 Bet On Tesla's Profitability
text: Two high-profile short sellers are making a friendly bet for charity on whether or not Tesla Inc (NASDAQ: TSLA) will turn a profit in any quarter of 2019.

title: Tesla Reverses Plans To Close Stores, Will Raise Prices Instead
text: Tesla stock was up Monday, following the announcement late Sunday that it will reverse plans to close U.S. stores. Instead, the car maker will raise prices on its high-end vehicles by about 3%.

Musk must respond to an order from a judge explaining why the court shouldn't hold him in contempt after he posted a tweet in February that some say may cost the CEO his title in the company.
